<p style="font-family:georgia;font-size:18px;text-align:center;"><i>
(10) The brothers immediately sent Paul and Silas away by night to Berea, and when they arrived they went into the Jewish synagogue. (11) Now these Jews were more noble than those in Thessalonica; they received the word with all eagerness, examining the Scriptures daily to see if these things were so.
Acts 17:10 - 11</i></p>
<p style="font-family:georgia;font-size:20px;text-align:center;">The Berean Proposal takes its name from Acts 17:10 - 11 where the Bereans took it upon themselves to search the Scriptures for truth. The Berean Proposal was started to help provide relevant and powerful Bible study tools to those seeking truth. For more information, feel free to browse our site. All materials are provided free to all, and may God bless you in the study of His Word.</p>
 
